{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017SjKw6SyzQWdqao3mAA93J","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Summary of URL Routing for \"Runs\" Endpoints\n\nI've completed a thorough search of the codebase for all files related to URL routing for \"runs\" endpoints. Here are my findings:\n\n### Backend Route Definitions (Go)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 139-157)\n\nRoute definitions:\n- `GET /runs` → `handleRunsList` (HTML page)\n- `GET /runs/{id}` → `handleRunDetail` (HTML page)\n- `GET /api/runs` → `handleAPIRuns` (JSON API)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}` → `handleAPIRunDetail` (JSON API)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` → `handleAPIStepOutput` (step output logs)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` → `handleAPIStream` (SSE log streaming)\n- `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` → `handleAPIDeleteContainer` (container lifecycle)\n\n### Project Filtering Support\n\nBoth HTML and API endpoints support a `?project=` query parameter:\n- `/runs?project=/home/user/alpha` (HTML)\n- `/api/runs?project=/home/user/alpha` (JSON)\n\nHandler implementation in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`:\n- Lines 248-260: `handleRunsList()` extracts `projectFilter := r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")`\n- Lines 447-461: `handleAPIRuns()` extracts same parameter\n- Both call `h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), projectFilter, time.Time{})` when filter is provided\n\n### Database/Store Layer\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (lines 214-246)\n\n- `ListRunsByProject(ctx context.Context, projectDir string, since time.Time)` - returns filtered runs\n- SQL queries use `WHERE project_dir = ?` clause\n- Ordering by `started_at DESC` for reverse chronological display\n\n### Frontend/Template References\n\n**Main runs listing template:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`\n- Line 6: Project filter dropdown that calls `filterByProject()`\n- Line 55: Links generated as `/runs?project=` + encodeURIComponent(dir)\n- Line 65: API fetch with project parameter: `/api/runs?project=`\n\n**Projects overview template:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html`\n- Line 27: Link to filtered runs: `/runs?project={{.Dir}}`\n\n**Project detail template:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`\n- Line 8: Link to all runs for a project: `/runs?project={{.Dir}}`\n\n**Run detail template:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n- Line 3: Breadcrumb link back to: `/runs`\n- Line 103: SSE stream endpoint: `/api/runs/{id}/stream`\n- Line 128: API detail fetch: `/api/runs/{id}`\n\n### Client-Side JavaScript\n\nEmbedded in HTML templates with the following key endpoints:\n- Polling: `fetch('/api/runs')` or `fetch('/api/runs?project=' + encodeURIComponent(currentProject))`\n- Detail polling: `fetch('/api/runs/' + runID)`\n- Step output: `fetch('/api/runs/' + runId + '/steps/' + step + '/output')`\n- Container deletion: `fetch('/api/runs/' + runID + '/container', { method: 'DELETE' })`\n\n### Test Coverage\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go`\n- Lines 286, 325: Tests confirm `?project=` parameter works for both HTML and JSON endpoints\n- Example test URLs: `/runs?project=/home/user/alpha` and `/api/runs?project=/home/user/alpha`\n\n### Related Project Listings\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 474-523)\n- `GET /api/projects` → returns list of all projects with health metrics\n\nAll files are in the main codebase (not in worktree directories), with the primary implementation in:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (handler functions)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (database queries)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (primary UI)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` (navigation links)\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (project-specific runs link)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1100570ebec4d6fd (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 55116\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 27211</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d4b4a2d9-8019-45f0-bca8-a8ab5c24bdcf","uuid":"c3229e53-d83d-4858-8b34-ee8dccd545ff","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all files related to URL routing for \"runs\" endpoints, especially any route that handles `runs?project=...` or project runs listing. Search for:\n1. Route definitions containing \"runs\" \n2. Any URL patterns with \"runs\" and \"project\"\n3. Frontend links/references to runs URLs\n4. Handler functions for runs endpoints\n\nBe thorough - check both backend (Go) and any frontend/template files.","agentId":"a1100570ebec4d6fd","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have a comprehensive picture. Let me compile my findings:\n\n## Summary of URL Routing for \"Runs\" Endpoints\n\nI've completed a thorough search of the codebase for all files related to URL routing for \"runs\" endpoints. Here are my findings:\n\n### Backend Route Definitions (Go)\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 139-157)\n\nRoute definitions:\n- `GET /runs` → `handleRunsList` (HTML page)\n- `GET /runs/{id}` → `handleRunDetail` (HTML page)\n- `GET /api/runs` → `handleAPIRuns` (JSON API)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}` → `handleAPIRunDetail` (JSON API)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` → `handleAPIStepOutput` (step output logs)\n- `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream` → `handleAPIStream` (SSE log streaming)\n- `DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container` → `handleAPIDeleteContainer` (container lifecycle)\n\n### Project Filtering Support\n\nBoth HTML and API endpoints support a `?project=` query parameter:\n- `/runs?project=/home/user/alpha` (HTML)\n- `/api/runs?project=/home/user/alpha` (JSON)\n\nHandler implementation 