{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HNjvvzfHyzpSh6jg8Pp8kk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The old `handleRunsList` doesn't pass `ProjectLabel`. When accessed without a project filter, it should have an empty `ProjectLabel`, which is fine — the template will use an empty string. But if accessed with `?project=` query param (old URL), I should still support it for backwards compat but redirect to the new URL. Actually, let me keep it simple — the old handler can still work with `?project=` query param for backwards compat, but I need to resolve the label from the dir. Let me update it:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":368,"cache_read_input_tokens":37460,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":368},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"d4b4a2d9-8019-45f0-bca8-a8ab5c24bdcf","uuid":"460dd8a2-135e-4c77-9807-0dd4a5165b5b"}
